  "response": "The best times to drive for Uber X can vary depending on your location, but generally:\n\nPeak times with higher demand and better earnings include:\n\n1. Weekday mornings (rush hour, 7-9 AM)\n- Commuters going to work\n- Airport/train station trips\n\n2. Weekday evenings (rush hour, 4-7 PM)\n- People returning from work\n- Commuter traffic\n\n3. Weekends (Friday and Saturday nights)\n- Late night hours (10 PM - 3 AM)\n- Bar and restaurant crowds\n- Higher surge pricing potential\n\n4. Event times\n- Concerts\n- Sports games\n- Conventions\n- Festivals\n\n5. Holiday periods\n- More demand and potentially higher rates\n\nTips:\n- Learn your local market patterns\n- Track your earnings during different times\n- Be flexible with your schedule\n- Use the Uber driver app to see real-time demand\n- Consider driving during surge pricing periods\n\nRemember that optimal driving times can differ by city, so experimenting and tracking your local market is key to maximizing earnings.",
